<p>A <b>referendum on creating the post of Chief Councillor</b> was held in <a href="/wiki/Saint_Helena" title="Saint Helena">Saint Helena</a> on 23 March 2013.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> The proposal was rejected by 80% of voters, with <a href="/wiki/Voter_turnout" title="Voter turnout">voter turnout</a> at just 10%.</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Background">Background</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Saint_Helena_Chief_Councillor_referendum,_2013&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Background">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>In January 2013 the Government of Saint Helena published proposals for amendments to the constitution. This included the appointment of a Chief Councillor from the 12-member <a href="/wiki/Legislative_Council_of_Saint_Helena" title="Legislative Council of Saint Helena">Legislative Council</a>, who would appoint a further four members of the <a href="/wiki/Executive_Council_of_Saint_Helena" title="Executive Council of Saint Helena" class="mw-redirect">Executive Council</a> instead of the entire Executive Council being elected by the Legislative Council.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Results">Results</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Saint_Helena_Chief_Councillor_referendum,_2013&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Results">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
